Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel) and pop them on a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, add and season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Toss to coat then roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking. Halve the @burger buns{2}, and leave to the side.

Meanwhile, quarter the @pear{1} (no need to peel). Remove and discard the core. Thinly slice half of the pear and coarsely grate the other half. Trim the @cucumber{1/2} then quarter lengthways. Chop into small 2cm pieces. Halve the @lemon{1/2} and squeeze the juice into a large #bowl{}. Add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Mix together and set to one side, this is your salad dressing!

Put the grated pear into a #mixing bowl{} and add the @British pork mince{240%g} and @panko breadcrumbs{10%g}. Add a large pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} and mix everything together with your hands until well combined. Form the mixture into even sized burgers (1 per person). TIP: Make the burgers slightly bigger than the burger buns as they will shrink when cooked. IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once the pan is hot, lay in the burgers and fry them until cooked through and nicely browned on each side, ~{12-15%minutes} total. Turn every ~{2-3%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, pop the @crumbled blue cheese{30%g} on top of the burgers, pressing it down gently so it stays in place and turn the heat to low. Add a splash of @water{splash} in to the pan, cover with a #lid{} or some tin foil. Let the cheese melt in the steam, ~{2-3%minutes}, then remove from the heat. TIP: If you aren't a fan of blue cheese, the burger will still be delicious without. At the same time, add the burger buns to the middle shelf of the oven on another baking tray to warm through for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the sliced pear, cucumber, @pea shoots{40%g} and @walnuts{20%g} to the dressing and toss to coat. Place the burgers in the buns and serve with the salad and wedges alongside. Enjoy!